name: Run The Set
description: Run The Set is an event hosted by Incendium Gaming, that runs at the TMU Rogers Communication Centre in Toronto. The games they run include Street Fighter 6, Tekken 8, Guilty Gear Strive, Under Night In-Birth II, and Granblue Fantasy Versus: Rising. Please not that this event does not run every month.

name: In The Lab
description: In The Lab is an event hosted by the Mohawk Esports Collegiate Arena in partnership with Incendium Gaming. Their events run at the Digital Creativity Center within the The Joyce Center (also known as the EA wing) at Mowhawk College in Hamilton. The games they run include Street Fighter 6, Tekken 8, Guilty Gear Strive, Under Night In-Birth II, and Granblue Fantasy Versus: Rising.

name: Stun City
description: Stun City is an event hosted by Toronto Top Tiers, hosted at See-Scape in downtown Toronto. The games they run are Street Fighter 6 and Tekken 8.

name: Gourmet Bash 3.5
description: Gourmet Bash 3.5 is an event hosted by No Style Skirmish, hosted at the Gourmet Malaysia Restaurant in Scarborough. It features game titles including Melee, Guilty Gear Strive, Street Fighter 6, Tekken 8, Rivals of Aether II, Granblue Fantasy Versus Rising and Multiversus.

name: DKM Offside
description: DKM Offside is an event hosted by DKM Network in St. Catharines. They host Guilty Gear Strive and Rivals of Aether 2. For more information, please join the DMK Network Discord.

name: Just Mids
description: Just Mids is an event hosted at The Upper Hand in Mississauga. They alternate between running Guilty Gear Strive and Granblue Fantasy Versus Rising every other week.

name: Plus Mids
description: Plus Mids is an event hosted at The Upper Hand in Mississauga. It is a monthly-style event that runs quarterly. They host  Guilty Gear Strive and Granblue Fantasy Versus Rising.

name: Whiff City
description: Whiff City is an event run by the Barrie FGC in Barrie. It is a monthly event that is hosted in the CW Coop's restaurant. The mainstay games they host include Street Fighter 6, Tekken 8, and Guilty Gear Strive, with some variety games at different events.

name: DTR x TKO
description: DTR x TKO is an event run by Downtown Rumble in Ottawa. It is a weekly event with a different main game every week, hosted in the Level One Game Pub. Downtown Rumble hosts their brackets on Challonge, and announces them in the Ottawa FGC Discord, linked on the discord button on their Organizaiton profile.

name: Capital City Clash
description: Capital City Clash is an event run by Downtown Rumble and Battle City at the Algonquin College AC Hub in Ottawa. It is a monthly event, where they run Street Fighter 6, Tekken 8, Granblue Fantasy Versus Rising, Under Night In-Birth II, Guilty Gear Strive, Guilty Gear Xrd, and more. Please check either the Ottawa FGC Discord or the Battle City Discord for the Start.gg link and more information.

name: Battle City
description: Battle City is a weekly run by Battle City in Ottawa. They run mainly Street Figher 6 and Tekken 8 with some other variety games depending on the week. Please check either the Battle City Discord for the Start.gg link and more information.

name: The Local
description: The Localâ„¢ is the premiere melee weekly located in the heart of downtown Toronto. The venue is a great bar space with lots of good eats in the area and TTC accessible.

name: Perfect Storm
description: Perfect Storm is a new seasonal FGC event, held in the heart of downtown Ottawa! The event is hosted at the Ottawa Marriot Hotel. It features games such as Street Figher 6, Tekken 8, BBCF, GBVS:R, GGXrd, GGST, MBAACC, and more! Check out the start.gg for more information.

name: Get Louder!
description: North Bay FGC's first regional event! March 15th 2025 at OutLoud North Bay! They will be offering brackets for Ultimate (Singles + Doubles), Melee (Singles + Doubles), Rivals of Aether 2, Street Fighter 6, Tekken 8 and HamSumo. More venue information can be found on the start.gg linked below. Please note that event registration will close March 7th at 11:59 pm.

name: Poacher's Arms Weekly
description: The Poacher's Arms Weekly is a community event organized by the London Ontario FGC at the Poacher's Arms bar. While they meet weekly, they don't always have a bracket every week. They play a variety of different games. Tournaments are hosted on Challonge with on-site signups, so please check the London Ontario FGC Discord for more information.

name: Western University Weekly
description: The Western University Weekly is an event run by the London Ontario FGC at Western University in London. They meet in the University Community Center, room #65, although this room is subject to change under various circumstances. The event is in collaboration with WEGA, Western's gaming club, but it is open to everyone, even if you're not a member.

name: SMASH CLASS
description: SMASH CLASS is a weekly run by Smash Class at St. Clair College in Windsor. They meet weekly at the Nexus Open Gaming Lab in the main building of the St. Clair campus, and host games such as Tekken 8, Guilty Gear Strive, King of Fighter XV, Street Fighter 6, and more.

name: Boyceblue
description: Boyceblue is a monthly event hosted by the Windsor FGC. They meet monthly on Saturdays, and run tournaments each month, with a different game every month. They host practically anything fighting game related, so even if not many people play a particular game you might be interested in, you still usually can find people to play with. EVERYONE OF ALL GAMES/SKILL LEVELS ARE WELCOME! Please join the Discord for more venue information!

name: UWFGC Weekly Meet
description: The UWFGC Weekly Meet is a weekly event hosted at the University of Waterloo by the UWFGC. The event is open to the public. Every week to two weeks, they host a bracket, the game depending on what attendees want. Some games they host include Street Fighter 6, Tekken 8, Guilty Gear Strive, Under Night In-Birth II, Guilty Gear Xrd, and more.
